Sentencas: The metal exsolution of anodes was studied using spinel oxides of CuFe2O4 for enhancing the anodic activity of electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) at lower temperatures.
Titulo: Cu-Fe-Ni nano alloy particles obtained by exsolution from Cu(Ni)Fe2O4 as active anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: Moreover, Ni-doped Cu1-xNixFe2O4 (x = 0.1, 0.2, 0.3, and 0.5; CNFO) spinel oxides were investigated.
Titulo: Cu-Fe-Ni nano alloy particles obtained by exsolution from Cu(Ni)Fe2O4 as active anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: Although CNFO spinel oxides were decomposed by a reduction atmosphere, decomposed CNFO became a metallic phase with the exsolved nanosized alloy particles, which are composites of Cu-rich Cu-Fe-Ni and Fe-rich Fe-Ni-Cu metals on anodes, investigated using SEM-EDX, TEM-EDX and XRD.
Titulo: Cu-Fe-Ni nano alloy particles obtained by exsolution from Cu(Ni)Fe2O4 as active anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: According to power generation properties, the exsolved alloy formed from CNFO 0.1 showed the highest MPD of 670 mW cm(-2) at 1073 K and 120 mW cm(-2) at 873 K.
Titulo: Cu-Fe-Ni nano alloy particles obtained by exsolution from Cu(Ni)Fe2O4 as active anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: Compared with the Ni-Fe (9:1 wt%) alloy anode, CNFO 0.1 showed significantly decreased anodic polarization resistance, and hence, high power density was attributed to nano alloy particles.
Titulo: Cu-Fe-Ni nano alloy particles obtained by exsolution from Cu(Ni)Fe2O4 as active anode for SOFCs

Sentencas: Therefore, the metal particles on the metallic matrix exsolved from the CNFO spinel oxide are highly effective for active anode catalysts for intermediate temperature operations.
Titulo: Cu-Fe-Ni nano alloy particles obtained by exsolution from Cu(Ni)Fe2O4 as active anode for SOFCs
